  "prompt": "Who discovered chloroplast?",
  "response": "The discovery of chloroplasts is attributed to several scientists over time, as they were identified and studied in various contexts. However, the term \"chloroplast\" was first coined by the German botanist Andreas Schimper in 1883. Schimper was among the first to describe these organelles within plant cells and proposed their role in photosynthesis.\n\nPrior to Schimper, other researchers had observed structures within plant cells that are now known to be chloroplasts. For example, the fact that plant cells contain green pigment (chlorophyll) and perform photosynthesis had been recognized, but it was Schimper who identified and named the organelles as chloroplasts.\n\nOverall, the understanding of chloroplasts was developed progressively through the contributions of many scientists over time.",
